# Product Vision — iLink Ultra Virtualization

## 1. Overview

The iLink Ultra Virtualization product is a software-defined platform that replaces legacy physical iLink Ultra hardware with a virtualized in-site instance. It preserves core site controller and ticket validation functionality while removing hardware sourcing risk, simplifying deployment, and enabling more efficient operations. This solution is designed to address the market gap created by aging iLink Ultra devices and to support regulated gaming environments with a modern, scalable infrastructure approach.

## 2. Business Overview

The current iLink Ultra deployment model depends on specialized physical hardware that is increasingly difficult to source and maintain. Operators face long lead times, expensive field service, and growing risk as the hardware reaches end of life. At the same time, gaming operators are moving toward software-defined infrastructure to reduce costs, improve resilience, and enable faster updates.

This virtualization initiative meets customer needs for a sustainable replacement path that preserves existing gaming floor workflows and device compatibility. It supports the existing business flow of EGM-to-site controller communication, ticket validation, session management, and local event handling while shifting the implementation from bespoke physical units to approved virtualized hosts. The result is lower infrastructure cost, faster provisioning, better monitoring, and improved business continuity for regulators and operators alike.

## 3. Business Objective

This product aims to:
- remove the long-term hardware dependency created by the legacy iLink Ultra physical device,
- provide an in-site virtualized replacement that supports existing ticket validation and site controller services,
- reduce deployment time, field service cost, and hardware lifecycle risk,
- enable scalable growth by allowing more flexible capacity management in gaming locations,
- preserve regulatory and security compliance in approved virtualized environments,
- improve operational resilience with centralized management, health monitoring, and recoverability.

