## 5. Scope

### 5.1 Included in Scope

- Virtualized iLink Ultra instance hosting the core iLink protocol stack and site controller behavior
- Deployment on approved in-site virtualization hosts/hypervisors
- Integration with existing EGMs and casino network infrastructure
- Maintenance of existing ticket validation, session management, and event exchange flows
- Migration support for existing physical iLink Ultra configurations
- Operational health monitoring and alerting for the virtual instance
- Recovery patterns for virtual instance restart and failover
- Support for secure communication and compliance controls required by regulated gaming venues

### 5.2 Excluded from Scope

- Any mobile validator or handheld UI solution
- New customer-facing mobile or tablet validation features
- Changes to primary ticket validation business rules or EGM transaction logic
- Cloud-hosted or external hosting models outside approved in-site virtualization
- Full replacement of legacy hardware with new non-virtualized physical devices
- Non-iLink virtualization initiatives unrelated to the iLink Ultra platform

## 6. Assumptions

- Venue infrastructure supports the approved virtualization host and secure in-site deployment model
- Regulated jurisdictions permit virtualized site controller deployment when security and isolation controls are met
- Existing EGMs and backend systems can communicate with the virtualized instance using the current iLink protocol
- The virtualization platform delivers required performance, latency, and reliability for gaming floor operations
- Migration of current physical iLink Ultra configurations to virtual instances is technically feasible
- Monitoring and alerting for virtual instance health can be integrated into existing operations tools

## 7. Constraints

### Business Constraints

- Solution must comply with gaming jurisdiction rules for virtualization, secure hosting, and validated device behavior
- Operational behavior and access controls must remain consistent with audited validation requirements
- Deployment must preserve regulatory evidence requirements for ticket validation and device management

### Technical Constraints

- Virtualized platform must meet real-time and latency needs of EGM and site controller communication
- Redundant virtual instances cannot violate host isolation rules (for example, not running redundant instances on the same hypervisor where prohibited)
- Network segmentation and secure connectivity must be preserved for the virtualized iLink instance
- The virtual solution depends on stable backend availability for ticket processing and event synchronization

### Regulatory Constraints

- Must respect virtualization-related requirements such as those in GLI guidance for secure host isolation
- Must avoid virtualization approaches that could be interpreted as remote desktop or circumvention of location detection
- Must ensure the virtualized instance can be audited and certified in each applicable jurisdiction